The instruments are the last breaths of the dying, turned into music.  
The food? Memories made edible.  
And when you finish your meal?  
You don’t leave.  
You become the next waiter.  
The next violin.  
The next scent of rain on old leaves —  
waiting for the next soul who doesn’t know they’re already gone.  

This is not metaphor.  
It’s the law of this forest.  
And the restaurant?  
It’s always open.  
